text.section:
In addition to the powers set forth elsewhere in this title, the University may:
Exercise all the corporate powers granted Maryland corporations under the Maryland General Corporation Law;
Adopt and alter an official seal;
Sue and be sued, complain, and defend in all courts;
Maintain an office at the place the Board of Regents may designate;
Enter into contracts of any kind, and execute all instruments necessary or convenient with respect to its carrying out the powers in this subtitle to accomplish the purposes of the University;
Subject to the provisions of subsection (h) of this section, acquire, hold, lease, use, encumber, transfer, exchange, or dispose of real and personal property;
Borrow money from any source to acquire personal property as provided in § 12-105(c) of this subtitle; and
In addition to the powers set forth in Title 19 of this article and subject to the approval of the Board of Public Works, borrow money from any source for any corporate purpose, including working capital for its operations, reserve funds or interest, and mortgage, pledge, or otherwise encumber the property or funds of the University, and contract with or engage the services of any person in connection with any financing, including financial institutions, issuers of credit, or insurers.
